===Noun Phrase===
'''Allemande Left'''

# ''(Square dance)'' Move in which two facing dancers take left hands or forearms, turn halfway around to the left, let go, and step forward.

====Etymology====
From French '''[[Allemande]]''' ''German'', originally from Latin '''[[allemanus]]''', + '''[[Left]]'''.  Contrary to some folk etymologies, this term does '''not''' come from the phrase "A la main" (by the hand).

